iolence, architecture, and political power during the formative Díaz era. From this portrait of daily life in Mexico City, he shows us the qualities that "make a Mexican a Mexican" and have created a culture in which, as the Mexican saying goes, "everything changes so that everything remains the same."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCity and town life -- Mexico -- Mexico City -- History -- 19th century. 0aCity and town lifezMexicozMexico CityxHistoryy19th century. 0aDíaz, Porfirio, -- 1830-1915. 0aMexico City (Mexico) -- Economic conditions. 0aMexico City (Mexico) -- History. 0aSocial conflict -- Mexico -- Mexico City -- History -- 19th century. 0aSocial conflictzMexicozMexico CityxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/74047140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292730755423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292730755/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK